    <div class="calculator">
        <input type="text" class="display" id="display" disabled>
        <div class="buttons">
            <button class="button" onclick="clearDisplay()">C</button>
            <button class="button" onclick="backspace()">DEL</button>
            <button class="button" onclick="calculate('%')">%</button>
            <button class="button" onclick="calculate('/')">/</button>
            <button class="button" onclick="calculate('7')">7</button>
            <button class="button" onclick="calculate('8')">8</button>
            <button class="button" onclick="calculate('9')">9</button>
            <button class="button" onclick="calculate('*')">*</button>
            <button class="button" onclick="calculate('4')">4</button>
            <button class="button" onclick="calculate('5')">5</button>
            <button class="button" onclick="calculate('6')">6</button>
            <button class="button" onclick="calculate('-')">-</button>
            <button class="button" onclick="calculate('1')">1</button>
            <button class="button" onclick="calculate('2')">2</button>
            <button class="button" onclick="calculate('3')">3</button>
            <button class="button" onclick="calculate('+')">+</button>
            <button class="button" onclick="calculate('0')">0</button>
            <button class="button" onclick="calculate('.')">.</button>
            <button class="button" onclick="calculate('=')">=</button>
        </div>
    </div>
    <script>
        let display = document.getElementById('display');
        let calculation = '';

        function calculate(value) {
            if (value === '=') {
                try {
                    calculation = eval(calculation);
                    display.value = calculation;
                } catch (e) {
                    display.value = 'Error';
                    calculation = '';
                }
            } else {
                calculation += value;
                display.value = calculation;
            }
        }

        function clearDisplay() {
            display.value = '';
            calculation = '';
        }

        function backspace() {
            calculation = calculation.slice(0, -1);
            display.value = calculation;
        }
    </script>
</body>
</html>
```

This is a basic calculator app with the following features:
* **Display**: Shows the current calculation or result
* **Buttons**: Allows users to input numbers and operators
* **Clear**: Clears the display and resets the calculation
* **Delete**: Deletes the last character from the calculation
* **Calculate**: Evaluates the calculation and displays the result

**Example Use Cases:**

* Basic arithmetic: `2 + 2 =`
* Decimal numbers: `10.5 + 2.5 =`
* Percentage: `10 % 2 =`
* Error handling: `2 + a =` (will display "Error")

